Reasoning: The paper focuses on evaluating the PredNet architecture for video action classification, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Additionally, the PredNet architecture is based on Predictive Coding theory, which is a topic related to neural networks (NE) and machine learning (LG). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the self-supervised video prediction aspect of the PredNet architecture, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper proposes an extended architecture for improving the model performance, which involves robotics (RO) as it aims to condition future frame predictions on the action class of the video.
